The answer lies in [the documentation](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/trigger-syntax.html):

&gt; In an `INSERT` trigger, only `NEW.col_name` can be used; there is no old row.

Other issues with your code:

- you are missing the `BEGIN` and `END;` keywords around the code block
- the `IF` block must be terminated with `END IF;`

You trigger should be expressed as follows:

    CREATE TRIGGER my_trigger
    BEFORE INSERT ON my_table
    FOR EACH ROW 
    BEGIN
        IF NEW.date = &#39;0000-00-00&#39; THEN
            SET NEW.date = NOW();
        END IF;
    END;

**[Demo on DB Fiddle](https://www.db-fiddle.com/f/P8gVpVbUABpRzHrUqWFuQ/1)**:

